We can't just rush into this.

54
00:04:40,319 --> 00:04:41,199
Then again...

55
00:04:59,180 --> 00:05:00,540
Just drag our feet on it for now.

56
00:05:02,339 --> 00:05:03,519
We can just issue

57
00:05:03,519 --> 00:05:04,639
a vague assessment.

58
00:05:05,259 --> 00:05:05,860
Anyway, until

59
00:05:05,860 --> 00:05:06,959
the final report stage,

60
00:05:07,360 --> 00:05:08,420
nothing is set in stone.

61
00:05:19,620 --> 00:05:20,399
Was it Chen Yi?

62
00:05:23,439 --> 00:05:24,379
Is he upsetting you again?

63
00:05:27,560 --> 00:05:28,199
Cen Ye,

64
00:05:29,420 --> 00:05:30,720
suppose there's someone who'd

65
00:05:31,040 --> 00:05:33,060
enter the lion's den for you,

66
00:05:33,819 --> 00:05:35,420
even if the cost is a promising future–

67
00:05:36,639 --> 00:05:37,620
Is that too much for you?

68
00:05:41,279 --> 00:05:43,060
I think a good relationship

69
00:05:43,759 --> 00:05:44,879
is about equals

70
00:05:44,879 --> 00:05:46,139
finding a true match.

71
00:05:46,660 --> 00:05:47,600
If you love someone so much

72
00:05:47,600 --> 00:05:48,680
that you stop loving yourself,

73
00:05:49,980 --> 00:05:51,600
you're just wrong for each other.

74
00:06:02,660 --> 00:06:03,439
- Hustle.
- All set.

75
00:06:03,439 --> 00:06:03,959
- You guys...
- Let's hit the road.

76
00:06:03,959 --> 00:06:04,519
I'm exhausted.

77
00:06:05,510 --> 00:06:06,733
- We got a crazy load...
- Why'd it

78
00:06:06,899 --> 00:06:07,680
take you so long?

79
00:06:08,439 --> 00:06:09,660
...of positions to process.

80
00:06:10,019 --> 00:06:11,259
I mean, wh-what's the point

81
00:06:11,259 --> 00:06:12,399
of rushing things?

82
00:06:12,800 --> 00:06:13,779
What a waste.

83
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:14,379
Let's go.

84
00:06:15,139 --> 00:06:15,800
Buckle up.

85
00:06:16,160 --> 00:06:16,500
Got it.

86
00:06:26,939 --> 00:06:28,639
About the truck license plate

87
00:06:29,600 --> 00:06:30,800
you gave me a couple days ago...

88
00:06:31,620 --> 00:06:32,199
I've had

89
00:06:32,199 --> 00:06:33,139
my team tracking it.

90
00:06:34,660 --> 00:06:36,060
As for the ship...

91
00:06:36,459 --> 00:06:38,160
Likely seasoned players from Gangcheng.

92
00:06:38,540 --> 00:06:39,740
We've scoped out the route.

93
00:06:40,339 --> 00:06:41,819
But these guys are shady.

94
00:06:42,379 --> 00:06:43,540
Every time we make a move,

95
00:06:43,839 --> 00:06:45,120
they clam up.

96
00:06:47,519 --> 00:06:48,959
I'm currently pushing for

97
00:06:49,630 --> 00:06:50,844
inter-departmental cooperation.

98
00:06:51,540 --> 00:06:52,759
Your only job right now

99
00:06:53,060 --> 00:06:54,379
is to keep eyes on this guy.

100
00:06:59,500 --> 00:07:00,639
If he's playing games,

101
00:07:01,899 --> 00:07:03,240
he'll slip up eventually.

102
00:07:08,639 --> 00:07:09,240
Zhou,

103
00:07:09,980 --> 00:07:11,866
things are different than they were six years ago.

104
00:07:16,939 --> 00:07:17,560
I know.

105
00:07:20,459 --> 00:07:21,060
Yi,

106
00:07:21,819 --> 00:07:22,560
this time,

107
00:07:22,819 --> 00:07:24,240
you didn't get the job done for him.

108
00:07:25,288 --> 00:07:26,911
Do you think he's getting suspicious?

109
00:07:29,360 --> 00:07:30,466
I wouldn't be surprised.

110
00:07:30,950 --> 00:07:31,888
He never trusted me.

111
00:07:34,370 --> 00:07:35,355
What about Kao?

112
00:07:36,100 --> 00:07:37,822
Is he handling the coordination himself now?

113
00:07:38,259 --> 00:07:38,579
Yes.

114
00:07:40,819 --> 00:07:41,890
He helped me out

115
00:07:41,890 --> 00:07:42,933
when I was at rock bottom.

116
00:07:44,060 --> 00:07:45,120
They found out about this.

117
00:07:45,540 --> 00:07:46,577
That's why I was targeted.

118
00:07:48,660 --> 00:07:49,879
They need Kao's influence

119
00:07:50,339 --> 00:07:51,680
to run this overseas line.

120
00:07:52,100 --> 00:07:53,319
And he kind of vouchsafed my

121
00:07:53,740 --> 00:07:54,480
staying at Haoyun.

122
00:07:57,310 --> 00:07:58,555
But after you crashed their party

123
00:07:58,639 --> 00:07:59,560
last time,

124
00:08:00,420 --> 00:08:01,488
given how his brain works,

125
00:08:02,270 --> 00:08:03,266
he's not going to let me

126
00:08:03,720 --> 00:08:04,800
get near them for a while.

127
00:08:11,579 --> 00:08:12,060
Understood.

128
00:08:13,519 --> 00:08:14,480
Don't dig any deeper,

129
00:08:15,240 --> 00:08:16,690
or we might accidentally

130
00:08:16,690 --> 00:08:17,555
drag you into our mess.

131
00:08:20,720 --> 00:08:21,279
I hear you.

132
00:08:24,860 --> 00:08:25,259
Yi,

133
00:08:28,300 --> 00:08:28,959
I know

134
00:08:29,690 --> 00:08:30,733
you've had it all figured out.

135
00:08:31,519 --> 00:08:32,679
Personally,

136
00:08:33,940 --> 00:08:35,559
I wish you could pull out immediately.

137
00:08:36,200 --> 00:08:37,940
But as Wen's husband,

138
00:08:39,860 --> 00:08:41,259
I just want to say...

139
00:08:42,879 --> 00:08:43,440
thanks.

140
00:08:47,600 --> 00:08:48,620
Don't get sappy on me.

141
00:08:49,980 --> 00:08:51,000
Shut up.

142
00:08:51,270 --> 00:08:52,355
I'm being serious.

143
00:08:55,390 --> 00:08:56,400
Enough about me.

144
00:08:57,799 --> 00:08:58,620
With Miao Jing,

145
00:08:59,039 --> 00:08:59,860
what's the matter?

146
00:09:05,899 --> 00:09:06,399
What?

147
00:09:07,080 --> 00:09:07,740
Did you have a fight?

148
00:09:11,240 --> 00:09:11,879
She moved out.

149
00:09:13,620 --> 00:09:14,460
Moved out?

150
00:09:15,940 --> 00:09:17,200
That's rough.

151
00:09:18,519 --> 00:09:19,799
Must be pretty serious then.

152
00:09:20,370 --> 00:09:21,511
Ever tried sweet-talking?

153
00:09:21,840 --> 00:09:23,159
If that would fix it,

154
00:09:23,159 --> 00:09:24,360
she wouldn't have left.

155
00:09:29,340 --> 00:09:30,500
She's just like Wen.

156
00:09:31,379 --> 00:09:32,179
I remember

157
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:34,120
if I pissed her off

158
00:09:34,639 --> 00:09:35,779
and it was no big deal,

159
00:09:37,100 --> 00:09:38,555
she'd throw a half-hearted tantrum and

160
00:09:39,150 --> 00:09:39,955
act a tad dramatic,

161
00:09:40,320 --> 00:09:41,800
but I always get to make it up to her.

162
00:09:42,039 --> 00:09:43,740
But if you truly cross her line,

163
00:09:44,820 --> 00:09:45,779
she's cold as ice.

164
00:09:46,510 --> 00:09:47,822
That's when the "sweet talking"

165
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:49,066
outstay their welcome.

166
00:09:55,580 --> 00:09:56,220
So what do I do?

167
00:09:57,639 --> 00:09:58,320
What do you do?

168
00:10:00,039 --> 00:10:01,200
You keep at it.

169
00:10:01,539 --> 00:10:02,440
Get on your knees,

170
00:10:02,440 --> 00:10:03,379
wait for an opening,

171
00:10:03,500 --> 00:10:04,500
and cry your heart out.

172
00:10:07,059 --> 00:10:08,259
You blockhead.

173
00:10:08,659 --> 00:10:10,379
Stop making her concerned.

174
00:10:11,620 --> 00:10:12,899
If you keep staying on the fence,

175
00:10:12,899 --> 00:10:14,200
you can kiss her goodbye.

176
00:10:14,480 --> 00:10:15,120
You know?

177
00:10:17,960 --> 00:10:18,740
Cat got your tongue?

178
00:10:19,220 --> 00:10:19,820
Keep playing.

179
00:10:20,440 --> 00:10:21,559
If you manage to beat me,

180
00:10:22,240 --> 00:10:23,360
maybe Miao Jing will come back.

181
00:10:27,919 --> 00:10:29,039
I'll give you a long one.

182
00:10:42,899 --> 00:10:44,299
Vehicle tax, property tax,

183
00:10:44,299 --> 00:10:46,179
and land appreciation tax all goes through the P&L.

184
00:10:46,379 --> 00:10:47,639
They're carried forward from last year.

185
00:10:47,960 --> 00:10:48,960
And about resource tax and

186
00:10:48,960 --> 00:10:49,519
consumption tax,

187
00:10:49,519 --> 00:10:50,139
no loss

188
00:10:50,139 --> 00:10:50,720
carryforwards.

189
00:10:51,740 --> 00:10:52,340
That should be all.

190
00:10:52,340 --> 00:10:53,740
Damn it.

191
00:10:55,460 --> 00:10:56,539
The last couple of months

192
00:10:56,539 --> 00:10:58,500
felt like decades.

193
00:10:59,580 --> 00:11:00,320
How's things on your end?

194
00:11:00,919 --> 00:11:02,320
A faint light at the end of the tunnel.

195
00:11:03,740 --> 00:11:06,259
I really miss my pork mooncakes,

196
00:11:06,600 --> 00:11:08,480
palmiers and scallion oil noodles.

197
00:11:08,879 --> 00:11:09,620
Just how you miss

198
00:11:09,620 --> 00:11:10,539
someone in particular.

199
00:11:12,120 --> 00:11:12,820
What did you say?

200
00:11:14,019 --> 00:11:16,299
I said once you get back to Haicheng,

201
00:11:16,299 --> 00:11:17,659
you're gonna miss badly the

202
00:11:18,159 --> 00:11:18,740
Rice noodle rolls, wontons,

203
00:11:18,740 --> 00:11:19,460
and the beef meatballs here.

204
00:11:24,000 --> 00:11:24,519
Ma Yang?

205
00:11:25,679 --> 00:11:26,080
What?

206
00:11:26,080 --> 00:11:27,059
Quit staring at me.

207
00:11:27,059 --> 00:11:28,059
You're freaking me out.

208
00:11:28,220 --> 00:11:29,360
You've got real potential.

209
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:30,799
What kind of potential?

210
00:11:31,279 --> 00:11:33,279
Potential to hang with Ding Lei.

211
00:11:33,799 --> 00:11:35,120
Being that insufferable

212
00:11:35,120 --> 00:11:36,580
is a real talent.

213
00:11:37,720 --> 00:11:38,320
Boss,

214
00:11:39,399 --> 00:11:40,419
she's bullying me.

215
00:11:41,059 --> 00:11:42,139
I'll dump her for dinner.

216
00:11:42,139 --> 00:11:43,059
I'm eating with you.

217
00:11:43,320 --> 00:11:44,299
Get lost, because

218
00:11:44,299 --> 00:11:45,240
I've got plans tonight.

219
00:11:48,460 --> 00:11:49,940
Looks like

220
00:11:50,299 --> 00:11:51,500
all is not as single as you.

221
00:11:51,500 --> 00:11:52,820
Jing already told me—

222
00:11:53,580 --> 00:11:56,100
she's quote unquote "got plans tonight", too.

223
00:11:56,890 --> 00:11:58,155
Who'd you think it is?

224
00:12:01,860 --> 00:12:03,399
Boss's got the lucky man glow again.

225
00:12:04,019 --> 00:12:05,220
Alright. Go grab some food.

226
00:12:05,299 --> 00:12:05,899
After that,

227
00:12:06,120 --> 00:12:07,288
we're gonna wrap it up in...

228
00:12:07,879 --> 00:12:08,259
Extra hours.

229
00:12:08,340 --> 00:12:08,720
Wh–

230
00:12:16,840 --> 00:12:17,700
You've officially

231
00:12:17,700 --> 00:12:18,755
stepped on someone's toes.

232
00:12:28,220 --> 00:12:29,220
Been swamped lately?

233
00:12:30,860 --> 00:12:32,480
I missed when you'd dropped by and

234
00:12:32,899 --> 00:12:34,580
we'd go fishing or play a round.

235
00:12:37,480 --> 00:12:38,539
Just the usual workload.

236
00:12:39,379 --> 00:12:40,419
Whether I'm busy or not

237
00:12:40,700 --> 00:12:41,879
is all your call, isn't it?

238
00:12:42,559 --> 00:12:44,159
Mr. Liu called me to say

239
00:12:44,159 --> 00:12:44,700
thank you.

240
00:12:45,519 --> 00:12:46,779
That shipment

241
00:12:46,879 --> 00:12:48,440
almost caught the cops' attention.

242
00:12:48,860 --> 00:12:50,039
Glad you were there

243
00:12:50,500 --> 00:12:52,659
to smooth things over and save the day.

244
00:12:53,340 --> 00:12:53,860
Chen Yi,

245
00:12:55,899 --> 00:12:57,100
are you really on my side?

246
00:12:58,100 --> 00:12:58,899
What do you think?

247
00:12:59,639 --> 00:13:00,720
I trust you, of course.

248
00:13:01,580 --> 00:13:03,259
We've been through thick and thin

249
00:13:04,240 --> 00:13:05,740
over the years.

250
00:13:05,740 --> 00:13:06,899
We've seen it all together.

251
00:13:06,899 --> 00:13:08,419
The company wouldn't be here today

252
00:13:09,220 --> 00:13:10,460
if not for your hard work.

253
00:13:13,440 --> 00:13:14,019
Take a look.

254
00:13:20,179 --> 00:13:21,899
These audit risk warnings

255
00:13:21,899 --> 00:13:23,620
are getting more horrifying by the day.

256
00:13:25,419 --> 00:13:26,460
I was concerned

257
00:13:26,779 --> 00:13:27,820
something might go south

258
00:13:28,539 --> 00:13:30,100
and derail our plans with Hongshen.

259
00:13:31,120 --> 00:13:32,379
But I talked to Miao Jing,

260
00:13:33,139 --> 00:13:34,940
and she said she'd take full responsibility

261
00:13:36,519 --> 00:13:37,659
for this audit result.

262
00:13:48,379 --> 00:13:50,059
I'm so glad you lent a hand.

263
00:13:51,600 --> 00:13:52,179
Chen Yi,

264
00:13:53,100 --> 00:13:53,620
remember,

265
00:13:54,740 --> 00:13:55,700
we're in this together.

266
00:13:58,419 --> 00:13:59,620
We sink or swim together.

267
00:14:21,039 --> 00:14:21,620
Mr. Chen,

268
00:14:22,080 --> 00:14:23,080
any more questions?

269
00:14:25,440 --> 00:14:26,600
I've reviewed the reports.

270
00:14:27,059 --> 00:14:27,799
Flawless.

271
00:14:28,259 --> 00:14:29,299
Just a few spots

272
00:14:29,940 --> 00:14:30,700
I'm not sure about.

273
00:14:30,960 --> 00:14:31,460
What are they?

274
00:14:32,700 --> 00:14:33,940
The risks seemed a little bit

275
00:14:34,399 --> 00:14:35,059
overstated.

276
00:14:36,340 --> 00:14:37,340
As the auditors,

277
00:14:37,639 --> 00:14:38,419
we must ensure

278
00:14:38,419 --> 00:14:40,460
our findings are impartial and accurate.

279
00:14:40,759 --> 00:14:42,399
We are simply providing a well-informed

280
00:14:42,639 --> 00:14:44,139
warning about potential risks

281
00:14:44,240 --> 00:14:45,519
and vulnerabilities.

282
00:14:45,919 --> 00:14:46,419
Of course,

283
00:14:46,899 --> 00:14:47,620
this serves merely

284
00:14:47,620 --> 00:14:49,440
as reference for Hongshen

285
00:14:49,659 --> 00:14:50,440
to evaluate

286
00:14:50,700 --> 00:14:52,580
whether Haoyun Logistics

287
00:14:52,580 --> 00:14:53,250
can maintain

288
00:14:53,250 --> 00:14:54,511
healthy operations during funding.

289
00:14:55,080 --> 00:14:56,019
Looks like auditing takes

290
00:14:56,840 --> 00:14:58,100
quite some guts and skills.

291
00:15:06,240 --> 00:15:07,659
[The tension in here is suffocating.]

